# grapher_curve_stress.numos — WARNING-ONLY visual-stress capture (Phase 9D).
#
# Commits the curved function y=x^2 and renders it on the Graph tab so the curve
# rasterizer (GraphView sampleFuncAdaptive + fastDrawLine) can be inspected for
# visual quality: smoothness of the parabola, sample density near the vertex,
# line weight, and clipping at the viewport edges. y=x (the existing graph smoke)
# is a straight line and does not exercise curvature.
#
# This script is DELIBERATELY NOT wired into CI: it is NOT in
# generate-emulator-candidates.py's CANDIDATES list and is NOT named
# calc_semantic_* — so per the emulator test-script gating it neither gates CI nor
# blesses a golden. It exists purely for human visual review of curve quality and
# makes NO golden/mask claim.
#
# Key sequence mirrors grapher_graph_smoke, but commits y=x^2:
#   down  : TAB_BAR -> CONTENT (Add row)
#   enter : addFunction() -> startEditing() slot 0
#   y = x ^ 2 : insert y=x^2  (^ = KeyCode::POW, 2 = KeyCode::NUM_2)
#   enter : commit -> parsed valid (contains '=' so it is a plottable function)
#   graph : switchTab(Tab::GRAPH) -> createGraphPanel + native Kandinsky buffer
#   ac 0  : flush the app's deferred first replot at the default [-10,10]x[-7,7]
#           viewport WITHOUT pan/zoom/trace (same neutral flush as graph smoke)
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_curve_stress.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/grapher_curve_stress.ppm --quiet

log "grapher_curve_stress: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

open_app Grapher
wait 60

key down
key enter
key y
key =
key x
key ^
key 2
key enter
wait 80

key graph
wait 120

key ac
key 0
wait 180

screenshot out/grapher_curve_stress.ppm
log "grapher_curve_stress: screenshot captured"

assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_curve_stress: assertion passed (Grapher active, y=x^2 plotted)"
